Another one of the challenges, the first immunity challenge: how it works is each tribe is take to a cliff, at the bottom of the cliff in the water are 16 crates, 8 crates for each team. Each tribe member will take turns jumping into the water and untying the crate, then they can make their way to the beach, once they start making they're way to the each it's time for the next person to jump in. Every character ends up with a crate, it make be a challenge to untie or swim with the creat, but they all get a crate. The first tribe to get them to the spot on the beach and align them in the right oder wins the challenge. There can be some chaos when people are swimming, several people may be swimming back to shore at once. Character can jump in immediately after the person in front finished untying and is only just started swimming back to shore. The crates each have part of a pattern on it, and once all 8 creats are brough back to the shore, it's like an 8 peice puzzle. There's only 8 pieces so the puzzle part isn't that difficult.
